reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 25, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A perfect replacement. Better than the original
reviews.reviewText: I love my Samsung range, except for one thing: the knobs. They tend to break in a particular way after fairly short use. The reason they break is because the inside sleeve at the back of of the knob, the part that slips over the burner control rod on the range, is made of plastic. Every time you turn the knob, all the torque is transferred to that small diameter plastic sleeve, and being plastic, it tends to break it. My original knobs were failing after just a couple months of use. Samsung wants $50 to replace ONE knob. With 6 knobs on the front of the range, replacing them is a close to the cost of a brand new range. So the first thing I love about these replacement knobs is the price. Under $40 for five of them. The second thing I love about these replacement knobs is that they fit more snugly than the originals. They fit so snugly that at first, I thought they were the wrong size. I had a little trouble getting them to seat on the rod. But they aren't the wrong size. It just takes a little bit more force to get them to slide onto the range control rods. But once on, they don't 'wobble' like the original knobs do. This should also reduce breakage. Because the original knobs are so loose, when you turn those knobs, the internal sleeve is already rotating when it engages with the control rod, magnifying the bad effects of the torque. Even if I didn't describe that well enough to be understandable, the bottom line is that the new knobs fit better and seem more durable than the original (and they look exactly the same). And even if they end up failing at the same rate as the original knobs, the replacement cost is reasonable.

reviews.reviewText: I ran across these on Amazon quite by accident. These are really nice looking metal knobs, they replace the stock Samsung plastic knobs that look bad and won't stay attached after years of use with quality Stainless Steel knobs. There is no doubt in my mind that these LONGADS reinforced metal knobs will last me a lifetime! They look absolutely perfect! The metal reinforcing on the shaft connector is complete and runs the entire length of the stem making them quite durable as described by Longads. These are currently available for purchase on Amazon's website with lightning fast shipping and delivery. Installation took a couple of minutes, very easy and straightforward. I am not paid by, nor affiliated with LONGADS. These are my honest opinions and review of this product on my own oven.
